description:
Goal
Make the reuse model observable and pin the intended allocation/closure behavior with focused tests and fixture contracts.

Why
The dump pipeline exposed the current over-allocation, but brittle source/CLIF comparisons are not enough. We need event-based signal: how many reusable facts were born, transported, consumed, and how many runtime attempts fell back to allocation.

Telemetry changes
Add production-path telemetry, preferably under the existing compiler2/native/codegen event structure rather than a test-only dump path:

- reusable cons facts born at native lowering (`SplitList` birth count);
- physical facts transported through hidden continuation/helper captures;
- reusable cons facts consumed at codegen list-construction sites;
- runtime reuse attempts, successful rewrites, and alias fallback allocations if runtime telemetry has a suitable channel.

Tests / fixture contracts
- Runtime unit tests from the primitive ticket must remain green.
- Compiler2 native lowering/codegen tests should assert telemetry or IR facts rather than only string matching when possible.
- Fixture contracts to update/pin:
  - `fixtures2/behavior/enum_sort.fz`: fewer internal cons allocations; constant sorter/threading artifacts should not force extra closure/heap work;
  - `fixtures2/behavior/enum_list_allocations.fz`: consuming Enum operations should not allocate unnecessary list cons cells;
  - `fixtures2/behavior/enum_map_family.fz`: changed-head map-like reconstruction should prove generalized head+tail reuse, not just tail relink;
  - `fixtures2/behavior/enum_reduce_suspend.fz`: preserve the semantic suspend closure while eliminating compiler-internal continuation heap closures where direct delivery suffices.
- Use `./target/debug/fz2 --log-telemetry <path> run <fixture>` during development to inspect the event stream.

Acceptance criteria
- Telemetry can distinguish:
  - no capability born;
  - capability born but not transported;
  - capability transported but not consumed;
  - capability consumed but runtime fallback allocated due to aliasing.
- Tests fail loudly for the specific regression class instead of relying on broad allocation totals alone.
- Fixture expected files/sidecars reflect the new compiler2 contract and do not preserve old-world-only differences without distinction.

Deletion target
Remove temporary dump-only assertions or old-world-only fixture sidecars that were useful during diagnosis but are no longer the canonical signal.
